	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 22nd 1:16 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I know I am probably going to catch alot of flack for this and it is probably deserved as I have only played this one mage and it is only lvl 4, but here it goes.<br><br>I have been using this strat as an alternative to pets as they seem to sap most of my xp. I have been running around getting about 4 things on me (spiderlings, beetles, orcs, and wolves) then turning around and hitting them all for around 10 damage at the same time with Fire Flux (lvl 4 area damage spell) about 2-4 times to kill them all. I get about 2-3 blue bubs of experiance for ther Mass Kills and only have to med some back for about 10 mins before I go out again. This strat has earned me 4 times the amount I got with my pet in the same time frame. I have not died from using this strat yet, though once was very close, and I suggest doing this near guards. The damage I take may be offset by the fact that I have a full suit of armor (red Sr apprentice robe, mostly raw silk, and some cloth). I am going to keep experimenting with this and see just how far I can go before I have to start using my pet. <br><br>So there you go, my Mass Kill strat.<br>*Braces himself for the flames of criticism*<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
