<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99850257431544></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99850257431544><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99850257431544>RE: low lvl strat</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99850257431544#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=88899><span id= >Sumcaltim</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 22nd 1:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, it has been great xp, I dinged 5 in about an hours work last night. As for the interrupt problem, all you have to do it time it right. It's a fairly quick cast (1.8) so if you launch it off right after all the mobs get a hit in, you can hit em just right. The other things is, I put some points (5 I think) into stamina, so I have a little, though not much, more health at this lvl, and actually haven't been losing that much unless there is a bear on me. I am still going for beetles, spiders, and bears out in EC as that is the only place I can find a large enough concentration of blue cons to agro enough for the strat to not be a waste of mana. It is not as effective now as those things are not giving very good xp though. If I can find a concentration of lvl 4-5 creatures I can keep getting good xp. The other part of this strat that I forgot to include is that I strafe (hold ctrl and hit right and left) while I run and the mobs to not get to hit me (other than wolves) while I am collecting them. I hope some other starting mage reads this and tries it out. It gets great xp for this lvl. <br>&nbsp;<br>Master smith of Vallon Zek and damn proud of it!</td></tr>
